WEBVTT


00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:03.240
President Cyril Ramaphosa has determined Wednesday,

00:00:03.240 --> 00:00:06.480
May 29th as a date for the 2024 general

00:00:06.480 --> 00:00:08.300
national and provincial elections.

00:00:08.360 --> 00:00:10.480
Now the announcement is in accordance

00:00:10.480 --> 00:00:13.100
with the Constitution of South Africa.

00:00:13.400 --> 00:00:15.200
The president says he has a

00:00:15.200 --> 00:00:16.800
consulted with the Electoral Commission

00:00:16.800 --> 00:00:19.040
of South Africa on the election date.

00:00:19.040 --> 00:00:19.760
A furthermore,

00:00:19.760 --> 00:00:23.560
Ramaphosa says he has convened a meeting with all nine

00:00:23.560 --> 00:00:24.780
provincial premiers

00:00:24.840 --> 00:00:28.000
and the IEC to discuss the stage of readiness

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:29.500
for the general elections.

00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:33.160
Now the 2024 elections coincide with South Africa's

00:00:33.160 --> 00:00:37.060
Celebration of 30 years of freedom and democracy.

00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:39.880
Therefore, President Ramaphosa has called on all

00:00:39.880 --> 00:00:42.580
eligible voters to fully participate

00:00:42.720 --> 00:00:44.600
in this important and historic

00:00:44.600 --> 00:00:47.620
milestone on the South Africa democratic calendar.
